<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Challenge 1: The Hidden Secret</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="challenge-page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to Challenges</a>
    <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="EECS Girls Who Tech Camp" class="page-logo">

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <h1>👀 Challenge 1: The Hidden Secret</h1>
      <p class="desc">Mei built a personal webpage and hid a secret inside it. The page looks totally normal... but is it?</p>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-content">
      <h2>📖 The Story</h2>
      <div class="story-box">
        Mei just learned web development and built her very first personal homepage. She told her best friend: "I hid a secret in my webpage, but you won't be able to see it just by looking at the page!" As a future cybersecurity expert, can you prove her wrong?
      </div>

      <!-- ✨ Mei's Personal Homepage ✨ -->
      <div class="fake-website">
        <div class="fake-navbar">
          <span>🌸 Mei's Homepage</span>
          <span>About | Blog | Gallery</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fake-body">
          <h2>Welcome to My Homepage!</h2>
          <p>Hi everyone! I'm Mei. I love coding, drawing, and playing guitar.</p>
          <p>I built this website all by myself — pretty cool right? 😊</p>
          <p>By the way, I hid a secret somewhere in this page. Can you find it?</p>
          <!-- 🎯 Mei's secret is hidden here! -->
          <!-- flag{you_can_see_my_secrets!} -->
          <!-- Hehe, you found it! Right-click → View Page Source to see these hidden comments -->
          <p style="display:none">This is a hidden paragraph, but it's NOT the flag!</p>
          <div data-secret="close-but-not-the-flag" style="display:none">Keep looking!</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hint-box">
        <details>
          <summary class="hint-toggle">💡 Need a hint? Click to reveal</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;">A webpage has more than what you see on screen! Try right-clicking on the page and selecting "View Page Source" or "Inspect." Developers often use <code>&lt;!-- comments --&gt;</code> to leave notes in the code.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flag-form">
      <input type="text" class="flag-input" id="flagInput" placeholder="flag{...}" />
      <button class="submit-btn" onclick="submitFlag('ch1')">Submit Flag</button>
    </div>
    <div class="result-msg" id="result"></div>
  </div>

  <script src="/js/submit.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
